Katedra is a social paltform intended to facilitate communication between teachers and their students.</br>

Teachers are able to create isolated spaces for their courses, with the following functionalities, as for the moment:

<ul>
  <li>Invite members with a secret token</li>
  <li>Access rights - teacher / assistant / student</li>
  <li>Course description with header picture</li>
  <li>Message wall</li>
  <li>Questions and answers</li>
  <li>Instant messaging between members</li>
  <li>Upload files</li>
  <li>Give grades</li>
</ul>

<h2>Try Katedra on a demo server</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Redirect to the server "demo" from the root page</li>
  <li>Authenticate as an admin
    <ul>
      <li>Username: admin</li>
      <li>Password: admin</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Alternatively: create your own user</li>
  <li>Everyone is free to try all the functionalities on this demo server</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to start</h2>

<h3>If you are a teacher:</h3>

<ol type="1">
  <li>Subscribe for your own isolated server instance
    <ul>
      <li>Specify a server name - this is how everyone who knows the name will find your server</li>
      <li>Specify an admin password - this is how you can excercise admin rights in your server</li>
      <li>Pay the monthly subscription fee</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Redirect to your server from the root page using the server name</li>
  <li>Create a new user for yourself, receive confirmation via email</li>
  <li>Authenticate as an admin
    <ul>
      <li>Username: admin</li>
      <li>Password: the admin password you specified upon creation</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>As an admin, give "teacher" or "admin" rights to your newly created account</li>
  <li>Create a course, fill it with content (you can have multiple courses on the same server)</li>
  <li>Create an invitation token from your course</li>
  <li>Diffuse your server name and the course invitation token to your students via your own means</li>
</ol>

<h3>If you are a student:</h3>

<ol type="1">
  <li>Receive the server name from your teacher</li>
  <li>Redirect to the server from the root page using the server name</li>
  <li>Create a new user for yourself, receive confirmation via email</li>
  <li>Receive an invitation token from your teacher</li>
  <li>Join a course using the invitation token</li>
</ol>

